The paper deals with the problem of maximum matching in a streaming model, which involves processing data in a single pass and with limited memory. This is a classic problem in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM), and the paper presents lower bounds and approximation algorithms that are relevant to both fields. The paper also involves communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of randomized algorithms and analysis suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper's focus on approximation algorithms and space complexity suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) may be a relevant sub-category as well.
